    "narrative": "Our offensive outlook for April 9th is anchored by two high-efficiency starts in the outfield: **Jose Caballero** (77.16) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.98). **Jose Caballero** represents our premier play, benefiting from a favorable matchup against Springs; his score is buoyed by a significant platoon advantage and a slow delivery profile from the opposing starter, which creates a prime opportunity to hunt for our league-scarce stolen bases. Similarly, **Mickey Moniak** projects to thrive against the volatile Randy V\u00e1squez, with a +19% SP skill boost and a favorable promotion to the three-hole driving his elite efficiency rating. We are also monitoring **Giancarlo Stanton** (67.71) and **Max Muncy** (61.96), both of whom are strong starts due to favorable park factors and high-leverage lineup positions against Ryan Weathers.\n\nThe primary risk today involves the lineup statuses of **Vinnie Pasquantino** (51.61), **Mickey Moniak**, and **Kyle Karros** (48.59). While we have modeled these based on historical norms, confirmed lineups are pending; should **Vinnie Pasquantino** drop out of the #3 spot, his dynamic platoon penalty will further suppress his value, potentially pushing him below our preferred start threshold. **Kyle Karros** remains our most marginal start, and while he faces a high-xERA pitcher in Randy V\u00e1squez, his placement at the bottom of the order and a negative park factor nearly pushed him to the bench in favor of our depth pieces. Among those on the outside looking in, we are missing the production of **Corbin Carroll**, **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, **Josh Naylor**, and **James Wood** today, as they are either inactive or observing scheduled team off-days, leaving our remaining roster to carry the heavy lifting in the SB and HR categories.",
